#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:202
msgid "Type Promotion Differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:204
msgid ""
"Type promotion is the biggest area where NumPy deviates from the spec. The "
"most notable difference is that NumPy does value-based casting in many "
"cases. The spec explicitly disallows value-based casting. In the array API, "
"the result type of any operation is always determined entirely by the input "
"types, independently of values or shapes."
msgstr ""

