#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:816
msgid "**Breaking**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:230
msgid ""
"For example, ``numpy.array_api.asarray(0., dtype=float32) + 1e64`` is a "
"``float32`` array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:232
msgid ""
"In-place operators are disallowed when the left-hand side would be promoted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:235
msgid ""
"Example: ``a = np.array(1, dtype=np.int8); a += np.array(1, dtype=np."
"int16)``. The spec explicitly disallows this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:236
msgid ""
"In-place operators are disallowed when the right-hand side operand cannot "
"broadcast to the shape of the left-hand side operand."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:239
msgid ""
"This so-called \"reverse broadcasting\" should not be allowed. Example: ``a "
"= np.empty((2, 3, 4)); a += np.empty((3, 4))`` should error. See https://"
"github.com/numpy/numpy/issues/10404."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:242
msgid ""
"``int`` promotion for operators is only specified for integers within the "
"bounds of the dtype."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:245
msgid ""
"``numpy.array_api`` fallsback to ``np.ndarray`` behavior (either cast or "
"raise ``OverflowError``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:247
msgid ""
"``__pow__`` and ``__rpow__`` do not do value-based casting for 0-D arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:250
msgid ""
"For example, ``np.array(0., dtype=float32)**np.array(0., dtype=float64)`` is "
"``float32``. Note that this is value-based casting on 0-D arrays, not "
"scalars."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:253 ../../../reference/array_api.rst:719
msgid "No cross-kind casting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:255
msgid ""
"Namely, boolean, integer, and floating-point data types do not cast to each "
"other, except explicitly with ``astype`` (this is separate from the behavior "
"with Python scalars)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:258
msgid ""
"No casting unsigned integer dtypes to floating dtypes (e.g., ``int64 + "
"uint64 -> float64``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:262
msgid "``can_cast`` and ``result_type`` are restricted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:264
msgid "The ``numpy.array_api`` implementations disallow cross-kind casting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:265 ../../../reference/array_api.rst:782
msgid ""
"``sum`` and ``prod`` always upcast ``float32`` to ``float64`` when "
"``dtype=None``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:271
msgid "Indexing Differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:273
msgid ""
"The spec requires only a subset of indexing, but all indexing rules in the "
"spec are compatible with NumPy's more broad indexing rules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:282
msgid "No implicit ellipses (``...``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:284
msgid "If an index does not include an ellipsis, all axes must be indexed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:285
msgid "The start and stop of a slice may not be out of bounds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:287
msgid "For a slice ``i:j:k``, only the following are allowed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:289
msgid "``i`` or ``j`` omitted (``None``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:290
msgid "``-n <= i <= max(0, n - 1)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:291
msgid "For ``k > 0`` or ``k`` omitted (``None``), ``-n <= j <= n``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:292
msgid "For ``k < 0``, ``-n - 1 <= j <= max(0, n - 1)``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:293
msgid "Boolean array indices are only allowed as the sole index."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:296
msgid "Integer array indices are not allowed at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:298
msgid "With the exception of 0-D arrays, which are treated like integers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:303
msgid "Type Strictness"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:305
msgid ""
"Functions in ``numpy.array_api`` restrict their inputs to only those dtypes "
"that are explicitly required by the spec, even when the wrapped "
"corresponding NumPy function would allow a broader set. Here, we list each "
"function and the dtypes that are allowed in ``numpy.array_api``. These are "
"**strictness** differences because the spec does not require that other "
"dtypes result in an error. The categories here are defined as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:312
msgid "**Floating-point**: ``float32`` or ``float64``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:313
msgid ""
"**Integer**: Any signed or unsigned integer dtype (``int8``, ``int16``, "
"``int32``, ``int64``, ``uint8``, ``uint16``, ``uint32``, or ``uint64``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:315
msgid "**Boolean**: ``bool``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:316
msgid ""
"**Integer or boolean**: Any signed or unsigned integer dtype, or ``bool``. "
"For two-argument functions, both arguments must be integer or both must be "
"``bool``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:319
msgid ""
"**Numeric**: Any integer or floating-point dtype. For two-argument "
"functions, both arguments must be integer or both must be floating-point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:322
msgid ""
"**All**: Any of the above dtype categories. For two-argument functions, both "
"arguments must be the same kind (integer, floating-point, or boolean)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:325
msgid ""
"In all cases, the return dtype is chosen according to `the rules outlined in "
"the spec <https://data-apis.org/array-api/latest/API_specification/"
"type_promotion.html>`__, and does not differ from NumPy's return dtype for "
"any of the allowed input dtypes, except in the cases mentioned specifically "
"in the subsections below."
msgstr ""

