#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:529
msgid "Array Object"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:531
msgid ""
"All the special ``__operator__`` methods on the array object behave "
"identically to their corresponding functions (see `the spec <https://data-"
"apis.org/array-api/latest/API_specification/array_object.html#methods>`__ "
"for a list of which methods correspond to which functions). The exception is "
"that operators explicitly allow Python scalars according to the `rules "
"outlined in the spec <https://data-apis.org/array-api/latest/"
"API_specification/type_promotion.html#mixing-arrays-with-python-scalars>`__ "
"(see :ref:`array_api-type-promotion-differences`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:542
msgid "Array Object Differences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:550
msgid "No array scalars"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:552
msgid ""
"The spec does not have array scalars, only 0-D arrays. However, other than "
"the promotion differences outlined in :ref:`array_api-type-promotion-"
"differences`, scalars duck type as 0-D arrays for the purposes of the spec. "
"The are immutable, but the spec `does not require mutability <https://data-"
"apis.org/array-api/latest/design_topics/copies_views_and_mutation.html>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:558
msgid "``bool()``, ``int()``, and ``float()`` only work on 0-D arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:560
msgid "See https://github.com/numpy/numpy/issues/10404."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/array_api.rst:561
msgid "``__imatmul__``"
msgstr ""

